page.title: 11BYWAY'S COTTAGE
page.content:
{BYWAYS COTTAGE}
Byways cottage was built approximately in 1760. The cottage has been built in two parts, the oldest part in 1760 and the other part is unknown when it was built. We think Byways cottage is in two parts because one of the walls is very thick like an outside wall with a doorjam. The opposite side of that wall is at a different level of height. Inside the old and building there are completely different fireplaces from times set far apart. The services Byways cottage enjoy are: mains water electricity, and telephone but no gas or sewerage which means that all cottages in that area have a septic tank of their own.
